Lithium miner Brazil Minerals has been granted exploration permits for two additional mineral claims that are now part of its lithium project in the northeast part of the state of Minas Gerais, in Brazil. The company is focused on producing hard-rock lithium from high-grade spodumene pegmatites and now has direct ownership of projects in a triad of strategic minerals â€“ lithium, titanium and rare earths. Brazil Minerals also has a stake in Jupiter Gold Corporation.